rComments: EEB388 Pros: Very interesting course. Goldman is phenomenal, enthusiastic, very available clear and helpful. Cons: Need to memorize a lot. You will need to be able to recognize around 150 different skulls to familyl and know multiple adaptations per skull (and that is just the lab component). Have to learn lecture material in addition.

SMARTEST PERSON IN THE WORLD! Coordinated BIO150 with excellent organization, made Biome, FLC, and designed the U of T Biology Contest (very well made). His lab questions were hard, but they were fair. And yeah, he's often overlooked, so people should know him more.

Here's a really helpful guy for the elephantine U of T Biology course. Has the course pretty well managed, cares about the students a lot and is always coming up with Univ. wide initiative for students. His brainchilds include: Bio150 Course, Biom.utoronto Life Science Forums, FLCs and National Biology Competition.

This is guy is relaly cool, but he is often overlooked because he doesn't teach the course directly. He is one of the best speakers I've ever seen and he knows everything about the lab. He is a distinguished looking dude with a well defined chin and he's down to earth.  He doesn't make you feel dumb
